definition.value: The upper incisors deviate from the normal angle of being roughly parallel to the surface of the face and instead slant outwards.

A structural anomaly of the tiny blood vessels that connect arterioles with venules and whose walls act as semipermeable membranes that mediate the diffusion of fluids and gases between the blood circulation and body tissues.
Reduced resistance to rupture of capillary blood vessels. Capillary fragility may manifest as a bleeding diathesis with spontaneous ecchymoses (bruises).

A functional anomaly of the tiny blood vessels that connect arterioles with venules and whose walls act as semipermeable membranes that mediate the diffusion of fluids and gases between the blood circulation and body tissues.
A structural anomaly of nerves of the enteric nervous system.

Deterioration of enteric neurons with impairment of enteric neuronal structure. Typical neuropathological findings include qualitative (e.g., neuronal swelling, intranuclear inclusions, axonal degeneration) and quantitative (e.g., reduction in the number of neurons) abnormalities of the enteric neurons.
A functional anomaly of the digestive system.
A structural anomaly of the digestive system.

label.value: Abnormal morphology of erythroid progenitor cell

definition.value: Abnormal form of the progenitor cells committed to the erythroid lineage.

Anomalous form of the proerythroblast, i.e., the immature, nucleated erythrocyte occupying the stage of erythropoeisis that follows formation of erythroid progenitor cells. This cell is CD71-positive, has both a nucleus and a nucleolus, and lacks hematopoeitic lineage markers.
Swelling within the basal ganglia due to the accumulation of fluid.
Swelling within the thalamus due to the accumulation of fluid.
Calcium deposition in the thalamus.
A morphological anomaly of lymph nodes in the mesenteric root or throughout the mesentery.
Increase in size of one or more mesenteric lymph nodes.

label.value: Abnormal brain lactate level by MRS

definition.value: A deviation from normal of the level of lactate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label.value: Reduced brain lactate level by MRS

definition.value: A decrease in the level of lactate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label.value: Abnormal brain choline level by MRS

definition.value: A deviation from normal in the level of choline-containing compounds in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label.value: Reduced brain choline level by MRS

definition.value: An decrease in the level of choline-containing compounds in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label.value: Abnormal brain creatine level by MRS
Elevated brain creatine level by MRS

definition.value: An increase in the level of creatine in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label.value: Reduced brain creatine level by MRS
Abnormal brain N-acetyl aspartate level by MRS

definition.value: A deviation from normal in the level of N-acetyl aspartate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label.value: Elevated brain N-acetyl aspartate level by MRS

definition.value: An increase in the level of N-acetyl aspartate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).
A structural anomaly of the olfactory lobe, the structure within the brain that receives neural input from the nasal cavity and thereby processes the sense of smell.
Partial or complete wasting (loss) of hypothalamus tissue that was once present.
Multiple abscess lesions in the spleen.
Single (solitary) abscess in the spleen.
